# HomeAtlas Architecture

**Mission:** Luxury home care platform — not a window cleaning CRM. Document the **life of a property**, not jobs.

**Brands:** HomeAtlas (platform) · SqueegeeKing (customer) · Atlas (intelligence, `lib/concierge/`) · Headquarters (`/hq`). See `docs/BRAND.md`.

## Product flow

```
Marketing Website → Home Care Assessment → Member portal → Property Hub → Property Dashboard → Property Timeline → Visits → Photos → Atlas
```

Property Hub is where employee and member journeys converge. Property Timeline is the spine; visits and photos feed it; Atlas enriches everything downstream.

**PWA:** Member portal at `/portal/[token]` — Add to Home Screen. Mobile-first customer pages.

## Modules

Employee Dashboard · Technician App · Member portal · Atlas · Property Timeline · Membership System · Home Care Plan · Photo Library · Annual Home Care Review · Headquarters

## Core model

- **Homeowner** → many **Properties** (each fully independent)
- **Property** owns: Home Care Score, Membership, Property Timeline, Photo Library, Atlas summaries, technician notes, recommendations, services, proposals, documents, agreements, before/after photos, visit history, access info, custom notes
- **Property Timeline** is critical: every visit auto-creates an entry (date, technician, photos, notes, AI summary, services, score changes, recommendations, customer summary)

## Technician flow

Arrive → tap property → upload photos → check services → quick notes → Finish Visit. Atlas handles notes, summary, score, recommendations, follow-up email/text, portal update.

## Member portal

Apple Photos × luxury real estate portfolio. Production route: `/portal/[token]`. Demo slug routes: `/homecare/[homeowner]/[property]/portal`. Dark luxury aesthetic.

## People & team content

**All customer-facing people must be real SqueegeeKing team members or clearly marked portrait placeholders. Never stock photos or fictional names.**

- Founders: Noah Thomas, Dasan Gramps — `lib/team/founders.ts`
- Portraits: `public/team/{slug}/portrait-*.webp`
- Components: `components/team/`

## Nav (built)

`/` ↔ `/employee` ↔ `/properties` ↔ `/properties/[slug]` ↔ `/properties/[slug]/home-care-plan`

## Before building

1. Where in the **product flow**? 2. Which module? 3. Property-scoped? 4. Feeds the Property Timeline? 5. Luxury stewardship (not contractor SaaS)? 6. Thin slice only?

